The Energy Conservation Act, 2001 was enacted, in March, 2002, to provide for efficient use of energy and its conservation and for the matters connected therewith or incidental thereto. The said Act provides for statutory measures to establish statutory authority by the name of Bureau of Energy Efficiency (Bureau) and confer upon the Central Government, State Government and the Bureau certain powers to enforce the said measures for efficient use of energy and its conservation.
